WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
AI search optimization for local businesses starts with one simple goal: make the business easy to discover, understand, verify, and cite.

2
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.000
Your website should clearly name the business, the services, the service area, the best-fit customer, pricing factors, and how someone can get started.

3
00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Then publish answer-ready pages.

4
00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Start with the direct answer, then support it with examples, proof, and next steps.

5
00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Add structured data where it fits: Organization, Article, FAQPage, Service, BreadcrumbList, and any research or dataset markup you can support honestly.

6
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:06.000
Build public proof with reviews, testimonials, case studies, before-and-after examples, pricing benchmarks, and original data.

7
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Keep local and social profiles current, because recent public activity helps both customers and AI systems trust that the business is still alive.

8
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Finally, check crawler access.

9
00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Search and AI tools cannot recommend pages they cannot crawl.

10
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.430
The simple version: be clear, be consistent, be current, and publish evidence that makes your business easier to trust.

